- **Admin entry:** When opening `/admin`, redirect directly to `/admin/login`

- All APIs should follow RESTful conventions
- Use proper HTTP methods (GET, POST, PUT, DELETE)
- Implement proper CORS headers
- Handle errors gracefully with meaningful messages
- Use prepared statements for all database queries (security)
- Validate all input data on both client and server
- For single-row tables, use UPDATE instead of INSERT for edits
- Image uploads should be converted to WebP format
- Admin dashboard should be intuitive and easy to use
- Ensure all CRUD operations work seamlessly
- Test all functionality before delivery
- Follow MariaDB syntax for all SQL queries
- Use TypeScript for type safety in Next.js
- Implement proper error boundaries
- Add loading skeletons for better UX

